1183
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you today to accept responsibility for my actions and plead guilty to the offense of affray. As a 24-year-old individual, I found myself in a highly emotional and distressing situation that caused me to act in a way that I now deeply regret.

It is with great remorse that I admit to threatening my boyfriend at the bar where he was with his friends after discovering his infidelity. In a moment of anger and hurt, I made the impulsive decision to falsely claim that I had access to a gun and would use it against him if he did not disclose the name of the other woman involved. However, I had neither possessed nor had the means to obtain a firearm. Additionally, I must also acknowledge that I slapped him during our confrontation, though I caused no further harm.

I am fully aware that my conduct was unacceptable and that my actions caused fear and discomfort to those present at the bar. I deeply apologize for the distress I caused to everyone else in the establishment and acknowledge that I should have handled the situation in a more appropriate manner. I understand the impact my behavior had on those surrounding me, and I am genuinely remorseful for the disruption and fear I instilled.

I would like to bring to the court's attention that I have no prior criminal record. Furthermore, I am already taking steps towards self-improvement by attending therapy once a week. Recognizing the need for personal growth, I am committed to addressing and rectifying the issues within myself.

I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding, considering my guilty plea, lack of prior criminal record, and my dedication to therapy. I assure the court that this incident has served as a significant wake-up call, from which I have learned and will continue to learn.

To conclude, I acknowledge the severity of my actions and the impact they had on those present at the bar. I express my deepest remorse for my behavior and assume full responsibility for my actions. Moving forward, I am determined to make amends and become a more responsible and respectful member of society.

Thank you, Your Honor, for the opportunity to address the court, and I kindly request your consideration in this matter.
