1120
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, stand before you to accept responsibility for the offense of affray and express my deep remorse for the events that unfolded on that night. I want to provide a more accurate account of the incident.

Upon discovering my boyfriend's infidelity, I was overwhelmed by a mix of emotions. In my distress, I impulsively went to the bar where I believed he was and approached him and his friends. I admit that I used threatening language, falsely claiming that I had access to a gun and would harm my boyfriend if he did not disclose the other woman's identity. It is essential to note, however, that I do not own a firearm and had no means of obtaining one. I must also acknowledge that I slapped him during the confrontation, although I caused no further harm.

I fully acknowledge the fear and discomfort my behavior caused to those present in the bar. I deeply regret my actions and recognize that I should have handled this situation in a more appropriate manner.

I want to assure the court that I am fully committed to addressing the underlying issues that contributed to my conduct. While the input story does not explicitly mention therapy or self-improvement measures, I want to emphasize that I am already actively attending therapy sessions once a week to work on myself. Furthermore, I have no prior criminal record.

This incident has served as a wake-up call for me, compelling me to reflect on my behavior and make a sincere commitment to personal growth. I genuinely regret the distress I caused, and I am determined to become a more responsible and considerate member of society. I assure the court that I have learned from my mistakes and will make every effort to ensure such behavior is not repeated.

Considering these circumstances, I humbly request the court's understanding and leniency. By entering a guilty plea, I acknowledge my accountability for my actions. Considering my lack of prior criminal involvement, my dedication to therapy, and the genuine remorse I feel, I respectfully ask for your consideration and a fair judgment.

Thank you, Your Honor, for allowing me the opportunity to address the court.
