970
Your Honor,

I, Chloe Mills, come before you today to accept full responsibility for the offense of affray and express my deep remorse for the events that unfolded on that fateful night. As I provide a more accurate account of the incident, I would like to emphasize that my guilty plea serves as a mitigating factor that benefits the court.

In the midst of discovering my boyfriend's betrayal, I found myself consumed by a range of emotions. Overwhelmed by distress, I impulsively made my way to the bar where I believed he was, approaching him and his friends in a state of anger and hurt. Admittedly, I resorted to using threatening language, falsely claiming that I had access to a gun and would inflict harm upon my boyfriend if he did not reveal the other woman's identity. It is crucial to recognize that this claim was unfounded, as I do not own a firearm nor have any means of obtaining one. Additionally, I must acknowledge that during the confrontation, I did slap him, however, I caused no further harm.

I wholeheartedly acknowledge the fear and discomfort my behavior caused to those present in the bar. I deeply regret my actions and painfully realize that I should have handled this situation in a much more appropriate manner. I sincerely apologize to everyone affected and genuinely understand the gravity of my actions.

Taking into consideration the circumstances surrounding this case, including my lack of any prior criminal record, I respectfully request the court's understanding and leniency. By pleading guilty, I affirm my complete accountability for my actions. It is important to note that my intention upon entering the bar was not to inflict harm, but rather to express the profound emotional turmoil I was experiencing.

Thank you, Your Honor, for granting me the opportunity to address the court.

